ergetic leptons around the pulsar, we fitted an\nelectron diffusion model to the data. The normalisation of the diffusion\ncoefficient obtained of $D_0 = 7.6^{+1.5}_{-1.2} \\times 10^{27}$\ncm$^2$s$^{-1}$, at an electron energy of 100 TeV, is compatible with values\npreviously reported for the pulsar halo around Geminga, which is considerably\nbelow the Galactic average.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Apr 2023 17:54:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-24"}
