s with the same frequency and opposite wave numbers. Our estimate\nof the radiative flux generated from the simulation is up to $\\sim$ 30 mJy from\nan area of 100 km$^2$ for an observer at 1 kpc distance without the inclusion\nof relativistic beaming effects, which may account for multiple orders of\nmagnitude.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Apr 2023 11:18:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-07"}
